# Example Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values

# Supabase Configuration
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard → Your Project → Settings → API

# Your Supabase project URL
# Format: https://[project-ref].supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Anon/Public key (safe for client-side use)
# This is the JWT token starting with "eyJ..."
# RLS policies enforce security, so this key is safe to expose
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# Project reference (the subdomain part of your URL)
# Example: if URL is https://abc123xyz.supabase.co, then project ID is "abc123xyz"
VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-ref

# ============================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# ============================================================

# 1. DO NOT COMMIT .env.local TO GIT
#    - It's in .gitignore, but double check
#    - The .env.local file contains your project-specific values

# 2. THE PUBLISHABLE KEY IS SAFE FOR CLIENT-SIDE
#    - This is the "anon" key, not the "service_role" key
#    - Row Level Security (RLS) enforces permissions
#    - Users can only access data their role permits

# 3. NEVER EXPOSE THESE (NOT IN THIS FILE):
#    - Service role key (bypasses RLS)
#    - Database password
#    - JWT secret

# 4. FOR VERCEL DEPLOYMENT:
#    - Add these same variables in Vercel Dashboard
#    - Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Check all three environments: Production, Preview, Development
#    - See VERCEL_SETUP.md for detailed instructions

# 5. ALL VARIABLE NAMES MUST START WITH VITE_
#    - Vite only exposes variables with VITE_ prefix to client
#    - Variables without prefix won't be accessible

# ============================================================
# GETTING YOUR VALUES
# ============================================================

# 1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Click Settings (gear icon) in sidebar
# 4. Click "API" in settings menu
# 5. Copy values:
#    - Project URL → VITE_SUPABASE_URL
#    - anon public → VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
#    - Project ref is in the URL → VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID

# ============================================================
# VERIFICATION
# ============================================================

# After setting up .env.local:
# 1. Run: npm run dev
# 2. Open: http://localhost:8080
# 3. Check browser console for errors
# 4. Try to login
# 5. If you see "WebSocket connection failed", recheck your values

# ============================================================
# EXAMPLE (DO NOT USE THESE VALUES)
# ============================================================

# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://hntfeivuhmzdqlhtwxcn.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImhudGZlaXZ1aG16ZHFsaHR3eGNuIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NzI5NzY0OTAsImV4cCI6MjA4ODU1MjQ5MH0.kHpRKIjT7V4XsSW4atMRlh2k6SqB8ElOo5WH8-FNUBo
# VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID=hntfeivuhmzdqlhtwxcn
